==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sampler
<hw>Sam"pler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Exampler</er>, <er>Exemplar</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
makes up samples for inspection; one who examines samples, or by
samples; <as>as, a wool <ex>sampler</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pattern; a specimen; especially, a collection of
needlework patterns, as letters, borders, etc., to be used as samples,
or to display the skill of the worker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Susie dear, bring your <qex>sampler</qex> and Mrs. Schumann will
show you how to make that W you bothered over.</q> <rj><qau>E. E.
Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samshu</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Samshoo</ent>⟦br⟧
